entries.femaleVariant: Sheesh, looks like a kinda museum…
entries.maleVariant: Huh... looks like a kinda museum…

entries.femaleVariant: Heh. The Museum of Wishful Thinking.
Damn... There's no way around this?
Got a surprise for our guests. Makin' the final adjustments now...
And... we're clear. I detect no more -- Oh... God…
Myers – we gotta engage 'em. Song's on the case.
Hey… bad news this time. Hansen's dogs caught your scent, assault incoming.
What the hell is going on, V?!
Where the rich bought and sold so many unfulfilled dreams.
Time to roll up your sleeves.
Songbird, got a sitch. Can you jimmy the door?
You're not dyin' on me today!
The fall did. About time we caught a break.
Think I mighta cracked a rib.
That's all? Pff, you'll walk it off.
Buildin' seems to be in good shape. For Dogtown at least.
So quiet I can hear my chrome creak…
Want some good news? Not detectin' any hostiles in the area.
Strange, isn't it? Maybe Hansen found some rich fools to fund his whims.
Not quite. The place was built with Militech money. I was supposed to cut the ribbon on the opening day.
Meet the Chimera – a combat prototype from Militech's stables.
No need. Three, two, one…! Urgh!
Wonder what he's got stashed in here...
Something as dangerous as it is illegal?
Huh. One of Hansen's warehouses, it seems.
"A bright future – with the right financing."
Wars don't happen out of the blue. This – no exception, orders were issued.
So Militech sank money into Dogtown, too?
It was an urban renewal effort designed to curb Arasaka's growing influence. Militech backed most of the projects.
Whale of a building. What is it?
A gilded monument to a certain someone's bloated ego.
Wha - what the fuck is that?!
Who the fuck woke that thing?!
On paper, urban renewal. Under that cover, military infrastructure development.
Startin' to heat up in here, Songbird!
Working on it. Hold on tight.
Almost there, still melting ICE for override.
Scan it, V! Spot the gaps in the armor!
Yeah! That's right! We got it!
Shit! Not dead yet! Look alive!
Tech drones! Don't let 'em gussy up the fat one!
Concentrate your fire on the drones! I'll cover you!
Keep moving! Don't be a sittin' target!
Drop the bastard! Hit the exposed bits! It's our only chance!
But abandon all hope of hearin' a word of truth.
Heh… takes one to know one…
The fall wrecked it! Let's go! Kick this tin can to hell!
There has to be an exit here, somewhere…
Let's see what this beaut can do.
Uh-huh. Seen my fill of gonk-magnet ventures like this.
Huh, in a past life? What was it – real estate? Entertainment?
Arasaka, actually. Research and development, broadly speaking. Specializing in... "data acquisition."
Songbird's givin' us green for this place. We're good to go.
Grab what you can. And let's head out.
They must've geolocated the car you jacked.
That's not what it was called then, but yes.
Dunno, Song's havin' a fit or somethin'!
Son of a bitch went haywire!
For fuck's sake, So Mi! Slap a muzzle on the thing!
Eh… Phew! Close call, that. Heh, good teamwork.
And luck… A pile of luck, V.
You probably got spotted outside. Either way – get ready.
Take cover! Pepper it, elevator on its way!
Where brains fail, brawn prevails. Shall we?
Elevator on the way! Stay low till it gets here!
Keep 'em busy for a sec. Need that.
And spoil the surprise? No, no. no.
I'm gonna strangle you, So Mi! You're done!
Head for the elevator, just across the room.
Gotta find an elevator, other side of the room.
entries.maleVariant: Gotta find an elevator. Other side of the room.

entries.femaleVariant: The sucker's gonna blow! Kill it, now!
Jump on top and finish it, V!
Loose hatch, V! Now or never! Send it to the scrapyard!
Shit, bastards caught up to us again!
You wanna play rough? I'll show you rough!
Come on, you sonuva bitch! Face me!
Feel free to ask her 'bout those exhibits. Reeaally wonder what she'll say.
There's the Rosalind Myers I know. Never a shadow of accountability.
Mhm, on it... Ugh, the lock jammed. Gotta brute force it, V.
Wanna play rough? Gonna get rough.
